Data Scientist / Statistician		Ingo Money, Inc.		Greater Atlanta Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p><strong><span style="text-decoration:underline">Summary/Objective:</span></strong> </p><p>As an Ingo Money Data Scientist/Statistician, you will be part of a small, exciting, dynamic and growing team that delivers risk mitigation solutions and expertise that has a direct impact on Ingo Money’s strategic objectives and profitability.  In this role, you will responsible for the formation and application of modeling solutions combating various fraud across all product lines. </p><p>Realize your full potential and unleash your creativity and innovation as you join a team that fosters and supports an entrepreneurial spirit. </p><p><strong><span style="text-decoration:underline">General Duties &amp; Responsibilities:</span></strong> </p><ul><li>Develop, assist in implementation and monitor data driven models for use in real time fraud prevention. </li><li>Manipulate and analyze large data sets to detect fraud patterns and trends by conducting complex analysis. </li><li>Present results and recommendations to internal and external customers in a concise effective manner. </li><li>Work and collaborate with Risk management and various areas within the organization to develop the model strategy to solve business needs. </li><li>Provide insightful and actionable recommendations on process improvement that considers fraud exposure, customer service, and other operational impacts. </li><li>Work closely with development teams to communicate requirements and ensure quality deliverables of developed analytical solutions. </li></ul><p><strong><span style="text-decoration:underline">Education, Experience and Desired Skills:</span></strong> </p><ul><li>Master's or higher in Mathematics, Computer Science, Operations Research, Statistics or other related discipline. </li><li>2+ years of experience in a role as a Statistical Modeler or Data scientist with experience in DDA fraud, Identity fraud, payment risk, credit risk, ecommerce, financial services or other relevant experience in the analytics community. </li><li>Solid quantitative analytical experience using statistics, regression modeling, neural networks, decision trees, random forest, support vector machine, kernel based methods, clustering and similar methods to detect, deter and prevent fraud and other risk behaviors. </li><li>Proven ability to formulate new ideas for analytical solutions to address business issues and goals. </li><li>Proven ability to communicate and tailor complex quantitative analysis in a clear, precise and actionable manner for all levels or the organization. </li></ul><p> </p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Ingo Money facilitates the immediate, irreversible funding of payment cards, mobile wallets and bank accounts. The only technology solution of its kind, Ingo Money offers a convenient source of recurring funds for any payment platform to encourage consumer adoption of new and existing digital payments. The instantaneous nature of Ingo Money funding transactions means that regardless of their source, deposited funds are “Good Funds,” available to spend by the account or mobile wallet owner in minutes without risk.<br /><br />Ingo™, operated in conjunction with First Century Bank, N.A., is a consumer-direct, mobile account funding network accessible on iOS and Android devices via mobile application and embedded SDK. <br /><br />Ingo™ Enterprise is a commercial, white-label platform that enables banks and alternative financial services (AFS) providers to make immediate, non-provisional “Good Funds” available to their customers.<br /><br />Today, nearly three million consumers have used the company’s technology to access “Good Funds” from thousands of bank branches and AFS locations, ATMs, kiosks and mobile devices across the U.S.<br /><br />Good Funds in minutes. Give customers a new deposit choice.<br /><br />For sales or corporate inquiries contact: <br /><br />Chez Echeverri at 678-376-7012 or chez@ingomoney.com <br />See more at: http://www.ingomoney.com</div>